.

node.text:
Not gonna lie - I struggled at times with this drawing but the first rule of drawing in ink is to always finish!
.
Then I actually had a great time cutting this video because of all the nostalgia feels I got from listening to the “Tank” remix by Benjamin Briggs.
.
.
.

node.text:
🐸🐛🐏 Sea of Stars
Some more samples of the concept work I do for @sabotage.studio on Sea of Stars! Check their bio for a link to see more!
.
Credits to the animation team once more for their work on bringing my concepts to life — it’s truly one of the greatest honors I’ve had to see them do their magic.
.
@t_o__ot_/ -- Jean-Luc Savard (Most pixel designs, lead animator)
@martin.motion -- Martin Pare (Erlina, Antbruiser)
@ditheringheights --Thommy Snow (Erlina, Antbruiser, Garl, Giant Slug, Rochevre)
@brunopixels Bruno -- (Luslug, Srower)
Edouard (Main characters, Wyrd, Srower)
Sav (Portraits, Main Characters)
.
.
.
#gamedev #seaofstars #indiegame #gameart #conceptart #originalcharacter #characterdesign #artprocess #illustration

node.text:
👒🔪🌳Spring Stroll
Fanart of Édouard Manet’s 1881 “Spring.” The third image is the original — I’d love to tag him but I guess the dude doesn’t have insta yet.
.
Too late to make it into this shop update but we did upload a few more things we forgot to yesterday — Team Pocket and Pokemon Travel postcards!
.
.
.

node.text:
💙😑💤 Punkomon Poster!
Also on the shop is the hilarious work of  @laimakes — I helped her compile all 151 puns of the first gen Pokémon into a poster and I think it came out amazing. Get one for endless giggles and a great conversation piece!
.
Also, let me know which pun is your favorite because Lai and I have been guessing which one will be the crowd favorite lol. More sticker set possibilities??
.
.
.

node.text:
🌊✨🌙 Sea of Stars Concepts
A couple character designs I did for the upcoming game Sea of Stars! 
.
If you wanna see more, check out the lovely new compendium that @sabotage.studio put together — use the link in their bio to find the official page!
.
The process for most of my work on the game is pretty straightforward — ideation sketches, turnarounds, colors— but my favorite part BY FAR is getting to see so much of my work brought to life by the amazing animation team. Not all of them are featured in this post but I’ll follow this one up soon with more! Big shout out to the whole motley crew below!
.
@t_o__ot_/ -- Jean-Luc Savard (Most pixel designs, lead animator)
@martin.motion -- Martin Pare (Erlina, Antbruiser)
@ditheringheights --Thommy Snow (Erlina, Antbruiser, Garl, Giant Slug, Rochevre)
@brunopixels Bruno -- (Luslug, Srower)
Edouard (Main characters, Wyrd, Srower)
Sav (Portraits, Main Characters) 
.
.
.
#gamedev #seaofstars #indiegame #gameart #conceptart #originalcharacter #characterdesign #artprocess #illustration

node.text:
🏣👫🏻🏤👭🏻🏢👫🏻🏬
Some street fashion doods from a Nakey session hosted by @laimakes.
.
Some tips for studying photo references— once you’ve gotten comfortable with being able to copy what you see, STOP PURELY COPYING WHAT YOU SEE. Adding a small angle or pose adjustment can really help your brain to think in 3D instead of just transferring information. Also, pushing the expression can add a lot more story and flavor!
.
.
#doodle #sketch #procreate #digitalart #figuredrawing #nakey
